US-Romania duo wins mixed doubles at Australian Open
2012-01-29 08:35:57 GMT
MELBOURNE, Jan. 29 (Xinhua) -- American Bethanie Mattek-Sands and Horia Tecau of Romania won their first Grand Slam titles, after winning the Australian Open mixed doubles final here on Sunday.Eighth-seeded Mattek-Sands and Tecau overcame a nervous second set to beat Russian Elena Vesnian and Indian doubles specialist Leander Paes 6-3, 5-7, 10-3.Tecau, 27, and Mattek-Sands, 26, took control with a quick service break in the first set. Theu looked set for a comfortable win, leading 6-3, 4-3 before Vasnina and Paes fought back to give the Indian veteran a chance to add to the men's doubles title he won on Saturday night, after beating men's doubles giant Bryan BrothersVesnina and Paes levelled at 4-4 after a tight service game from Mattek-Sands. Then the American was broken again as the fifth seed won the second set to force a match tiebreak.Mattek-Sands produced a remarkable shot to open the tiebreak which momentum returned to her pairing. And the duo managed to close up the match in one hour and 42 minutes.It is Tecau's first Grand Slam title after three finals. He reached the men's doubles final at Wimbledon in 2011 and 2010, losing both times.
